libraqm
------------------------------------------
Raqm is a small library that encapsulates the logic for complex text layout
and provide a convenient API.

It currently provides bidirectional text support (using FriBiDi), shaping
(using HarfBuzz), and proper script itemization. As a result, Raqm can support
most writing systems covered by Unicode.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libfreetype-devel-2.6.5-1
  libfreetype6-2.6.5-1
  libfribidi-devel-0.19.7-1
  libfribidi0-0.19.7-1
  libharfbuzz-devel-1.4.8-1
  libharfbuzz0-1.4.8-1
  libraqm-devel-0.3.0-1bl1
  libraqm0-0.3.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/HOST-Oman/libraqm

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/HOST-Oman/libraqm/archive/v0.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libraqm-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libraqm-0.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libraqm-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraqm-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraqm0-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libraqm-devel-0.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libraqm)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libraqm.README
  /usr/share/doc/libraqm/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libraqm/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libraqm/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libraqm/README

(libraqm0)
  /usr/bin/cygraqm-0.dll

(libraqm-devel)
  /usr/include/raqm.h
  /usr/lib/libraqm.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/raqm.pc

